column21:
@Arnavion @pstratem So what does this do? The title isn't very informative and the code changes are a little confusing.
This obviously affects the calculation of the lag, but what does that fix in itself?
Also, does timeout have to occur only when the lag is bad? It also occurs after long periods of inactivity, doesn't it?

@TingPing But wouldn't any theme or script be super easy to update by just using find and replace and changing all instances of "Conection" to "Connection"? And all themes and scripts are easily editable, right?
I'm just saying having an announcement that there were some typos in the source that were updated and developers of themes and scripts need to update them (simply by using the correct spelling) doesn't seem to be that big of deal, at least in my eyes. I can understand not wanting to switch an entire codebase from one external library to another, or from one API to another, but this is really just a small enough change that I think the developers wouldn't mind it. Especially since most of them probably have noticed the incorrect spelling before.
Is there a repository or something of scripts and themes?

Umm...
if(line[0] == '=')
    program = g_strconcat("return ", line + 1, NULL);
else
    program = g_strdup(line);
ret_program = g_strconcat("return ", program, NULL);
becomes
if(line[0] == '=')
    line = line + 1;
ret_program = g_strconcat("return ", line, NULL);

#include <Windows.h> instead of __declspec(dllimport)
Put the calls to GetModuleFileNameA/W and strchr/wcschr inside #ifdef PY_3K instead of defining new macros for them.
And what exactly is this fixing?

The behavior of that arg on fe-text is entirely different than fe-gtk anyway. So I'd say that this should probably use the same directory: 


      hexchat/src/fe-gtk/fe-gtk.c


        Lines 194 to 205
      in
      7643022







           	if (arg_show_autoload) 




           	{ 




           		buffer = g_strdup_printf ("%s%caddons%c", get_xdir(), G_DIR_SEPARATOR, G_DIR_SEPARATOR); 




           #ifdef WIN32 




           		gtk_init (&argc, &argv); 




           		create_msg_dialog ("Plugin/Script Auto-load Directory", buffer); 




           #else 




           		puts (buffer); 




           #endif 




           		g_free (buffer); 









           		return 0;

