The script is not a big script (to see Main()) :
The first part of the script install the environment  to build (install librairies from brew only if is needed and environment variables (LD_PATH...) only if is need (like brew version of gettext or openssl that not linked with /usr/local/lib by default)
The second part call meson and ninja
The Thrid part make the bundles of hexchat.app and hexchat-portable.app
There are a few lines codes for patch some details.
It was the first time that i use meson and i spent a lot of days to understand how build, read documentation , understand that jhbuild is a old process for build it.
I taked the choice for don't touch the exiting code or meson.build files because i am not an expert and i don't want to maintain after ;)
But if you want i can explain to you which modifications is needed into the meson.build file for remove the patch lines of the script.
So if you can add this Script V1 into your tree could be nice. For me for the future release, and maybe for another people but that script and the portable bundle needs to be tested by someone else.
Also the part in the OSX folder of your tree (to make the OSX bundle) is Out of date if i understand because that continue to use jhbuild Right ?
Big Thks for your work.

@BlackDady I'm happy to help with testing. I happen to have a brand-new, nothing-installed Macbook Pro at my hands. Its at 10.14 Mojave which I can update to Catalina.
where can I find your latest build ?
PS: my other macbook is at Catalina already but full of homebrew and XCode and all sorts of dev-tools

